500. quisquam: sc. renuntia- vit. —— eho marks surprise. For another meaning of eho, see on 184. — an introduces the second alternative, although the first is not included in the ques- tion. — tute: emphatic3 con- trast the use of egomet which we have noticed in line 82. Trans- late “ Did you find out for your- self ? '' Davos pretends to be quite overcome with admiration of his master's shrewdness. There is irony in this and Davos’ succeeding speeches, but he is not now mocking Simo3 he is playing a part in all serious- ness. — intellexti: for the form, see on praescripsti (151).
